[16.180422, "o", "the skills currently available in this project.\u001b[0m\u001b[23;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[2m[\u001b[0m\u001b[1;96m+\u001b[0m\u001b[2m] \u001b[0m\u001b[1;97mIteration 1 / 100\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(30964 tok)\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(6.7s)\u001b[0m\u001b[24;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[2m  Think: \u001b[0m\u001b[2mThe user wants the skills available in this project. \"In this project\" points to brainyard \u001b[0m\u001b[25;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2mproject-scope skills. I'll call skills$list scoped to brainyard/project. A single tool \u001b[0m\u001b[26;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2mcall satisfies this with no post-processing needed.\u001b[0m\u001b[27;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[2m[\u001b[0m\u001b[1;93m⠼\u001b[0m\u001b[2m]\u001b[0m \u001b[96mThinking...\u001b[0m\u001b[2m (6.7s)\u001b[0m"]
